<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1461036" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=640%2C593&#038;ssl=1" alt="Edo polls: Do-or-die mentality, threat to free, fair elections — Buhari " width="640" height="593" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=1024%2C949&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=300%2C278&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=768%2C712&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=58%2C54&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=209%2C194&amp;ssl=1 209w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?resize=140%2C130&amp;ssl=1 140w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/FEC-5-1.jpg?w=1079&amp;ssl=1 1079w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday said that the do-or-die mentality to politics was a threat to free and fair elections because the actors are more focused on winning than caring about a fair outcome that reflects the will of the people. President Buhari in a message to voters, political parties, election officials, and security personnel, advised political parties, candidates, and security agents to behave responsibly in the Saturday Edo State gubernatorial elections. He reiterated his stance  that, “I am passionately committed to free and fair elections, but my own commitment is not enough if other actors at ground zero refuse to abide by the rules.” In a statement issued by the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu last night, the President said, “I want to see democratic standards in the country raised higher at every level, but these cannot be achieved when politicians resort to do or die methods to gain power by any means or machination.” He said that “the do-or-die mentality to politics is a threat to free and fair elections because the actors are more focused on winning than caring about a fair outcome that reflects the Will of the people.” The President appealed to all political parties and their candidates to behave peacefully and respect law and order. He also advised election officials and security agents “to remain neutral to ensure free and fair elections and avoid any action(s) capable of compromising the integrity of the elections.” President Buhari stressed that “conducting free and fair elections is one of my main concerns for our democracy, and I want this commitment to be one of the legacies I will leave behind when I depart office.” Vanguard IT was a special day on the road to the July 14, 2012 governorship election in Edo State. That was the day when contenders in the polls, who have been tackling one another savagely, met under one roof to deliberate with other critical stakeholders on modalities for ensuring a peaceful… June 27, 2012 In "Politics" Coordinator of Friends of Atiku Abubakar, FoA, Edo State, Dr. Isaiah Osifo, has said that President Muhammadu Buhari and his party, All Progressives Congress, APC, were not interested in a free and fair election. February 19, 2019 In "News" The Edo State Governor, Mr. Godwin Obaseki, has assured voters in the state of adequate security to ensure peaceful conduct of the rescheduled general elections, calling on the people to come out en masse to exercise their franchise to deepen democracy in the country. February 21, 2019 In "News"